  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Merchandiser",
  "description": "<p><strong>Key Responsibilities :</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Conduct daily visits to assigned retail outlets and various other locations as needed.</li>\n  <li>Develop and maintain strong relationships with store managers and staff at both the retailer and outlet levels.</li>\n  <li>Work closely with store personnel to prevent out-of-stock situations.</li>\n  <li>Understand and adapt to the Standard Operating Procedures (SOPs) and workflows of each retailer/store.</li>\n  <li>Coordinate with stores on promotional activities such as regular promotions, space buys, roadshows, sampling sessions, and festive events.</li>\n  <li>Execute merchandising, display setups, and trade promotions in accordance with our merchandising standards.</li>\n  <li>Replenish stock from cold rooms or back stores to shelves and freezers when necessary.</li>\n  <li>Where possible, assist in improving planograms and securing optimal product facings for our brand.</li>\n  <li>Propose and implement specific in-store promotional or trade plans when opportunities arise.</li>\n  <li>Monitor and report on the competitive landscape related to our products.</li>\n  <li>Perform any other ad-hoc duties as required.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Requirements :</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Willingness to travel to different locations daily; schedules will be arranged to minimize travel distances where possible.</li>\n  <li>Strong interpersonal and communication skills.</li>\n  <li>Up-to-date knowledge of current market trends.</li>\n  <li>Previous experience in retail merchandising is an advantage.</li>\n</ul>",
